title: PETA turns 35, still using sex and shock for animal causes
text: > Entertainment PETA turns 35, still using sex and shock for animal causes FILE - In this Jan. 15, 2007 file photo, People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals (PETA) demonstrators lie in fake coffins, staging a protest against the use of fur by the British fashion house Burberry in Paris. Posters read, "Even dead, we will not wear Burberry." PETA turns 35 years old in 2015, is the largest animal rights group in world with 3 million members, and has done a lot with a little sex, shock and celebrity.(AP Photo/Michel Euler, File)
